<span id="freeTextContainer10232944506048168982">The first thing you need to know is that this book is better than you think it&apos;ll be. The second thing you need to know is that things get meta-fictional quick. And it&apos;s awesome. Hunt creates such a vivid, beautiful landscape that you cannot HELP but get sucked in. And it&apos;s filled with everything you could want. Sci-fi? Fantasy? Gunslingers? Sea monsters? New cultures and races? You&apos;ll find it and you&apos;ll love it. <br/><br/>Ross is an easy narrator to follow and you really cheer for him. There are definite</span>
  <span id="freeText10232944506048168982" style="display:none">The first thing you need to know is that this book is better than you think it'll be. The second thing you need to know is that things get meta-fictional quick. And it's awesome. Hunt creates such a vivid, beautiful landscape that you cannot HELP but get sucked in. And it's filled with everything you could want. Sci-fi? Fantasy? Gunslingers? Sea monsters? New cultures and races? You'll find it and you'll love it. <br /><br />Ross is an easy narrator to follow and you really cheer for him. There are definite similarities to the Dark Tower but it's not pastiche or copying. There is a cliffhanger ending but thankfully, there's no need to wait for book 2 to come out (and it picks up immediately where this one ends). I'd talk more about the plot but beyond "Man ends up in another world," there's too much going on to share a whole lot. Read this book.</span>
